sub_title: 'Transcendent to be the Best' | Scaling Up coach at Scaleupp | Founder GoodUp, 1%Club, Nailab | Author De Poolster, Kilimanjaro als Medicijn, De Misbaren
summary:
Anna Chojnacka is an expert in building and growing highly result-oriented organizations. Her personal motto is: â€˜Transcendent to be the bestâ€™. She developed an â€˜adapt & thriveâ€™ approach to help you and your teams develop and execute a growth mindset that is not only highly purpose-driven as well as human-centric. Success that comes at the cost of (your own personal) health or at the expense of our world, is afterall a pyrrhic victory. 

The annual programs Scalupp.com offers, combines the proven Scaling up method with Power skills such as effective leadership and accountability. While the Scaling up method serves as a operating system to choose and monitor the desired growth drives, Power Skills fuel the behavioral change needed to speed up the envisioned rapid improvements further. Implementing a successful recruitment processes, mastering design thinking, OKRâ€™s and KPIâ€™s trainings for management teams are offered as well and integrated at need. 

With the help  of your Scaleupp coach â€˜focusing on the main thingâ€™ becomes a habit. Together we choose minimalistic data sets to successfully drive and manage the progress towards the desired growth in a structured and transparent way. 

The outcome? Focus, alignment and predictable growth. And above all: the space to enjoy the ride! 

The annual programs are offered in English Dutch and Polish. Anna has worked with more than 50 companies throughout Europe (a.o. Netherlands, France, Poland, Sweden and Monaco). 

References are available upon request.

PROFESSIONAL HIGHLIGHTS
Anna Chojnacka is the (co) founder of 1%Club, one of the first crowdfunding and crowdsourcing platforms in the Netherlands that has generated funding and expertise to successfully execute more than 1500 projects in 87 countries. 
The original platform developed into Goodup, that currently offers it as a SAAS solution and is currently used by Univeler, Mars, Deloitte and Booking and other corporates as Employee Engagement platform to â€˜do goodâ€™. She is also the co-founder of Nailab, a tech start-up in Nairobi Kenya. In 2018 Nailab was chosen as the launching platform of Jack-Maâ€™a Netrepreneur prize. She serves on several boards of advisors and was twice listed in the Top 10 most influential women in the Netherlands.

PERSONAL HIGHLIGHTS
In her personal life Anna is a proud mother of 3. She loves to write and has published 2 books, among them â€˜Kilimanjaro as medicineâ€™ about an expedition to climb the Kilimanjaro under the guidance of Wim Hoff aka the Iceman, in less than 48h, dressed in nothing more than shorts and a t-shirt.
